					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Usually 480i fields are blurred a bit vertically to minimize interline <a href="https://twitter.com/PinoBatch" class="postlink"><img src="https://twitter.com/favicon.ico" alt="Image" /></a> twitter when a scanline is noticeably brighter or darker than its neighbors.<br /><br /><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interlaced_video#Interline_twitter" class="postlink"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f0/Indian_Head_interlace.gif" alt="Image" /><br />Interline twitter</a><br />From left to right: original, interlaced, line doubled. Top row: not blurred; bottom row: blurred.<br /><br />That's why <em>Super Smash Bros. Melee</em> and <em>Brawl</em> have the deflicker switch to enable or disable the GameCube/Wii video DAC's vertical blur feature. Turning it on blurs everything and is good for CRTs; turning it off is better for LCDs that know how to weave when needed.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

